@page "/figure-image"
<PageTitle>Figure &amp; Image - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="figure-image">Figure &amp; Image</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="img">Img</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Img component renders an img element. The Image alias is also available.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;Img Src="photo.jpg" AriaLabel="A scenic landscape" /&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="figure">Figure</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Figure component wraps an image with a caption using the semantic figure element.
            </p>

            <pre><code>&lt;Figure&gt;
    &lt;Img Src="diagram.png" /&gt;
&lt;/Figure&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="parameters">Parameters</h2>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Src</td><td>string?</td><td>Image source URL (Img only).</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Class</td><td>string?</td><td>Additional CSS classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>AriaLabel</td><td>string?</td><td>Accessibility label.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>ChildContent</td><td>RenderFragment</td><td>Figure child content.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="figure-image-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Figure &amp; Image</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Figure &amp; Image</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the Figure component maps to Bootstrap's figure class and the
                Img component inside it maps to figure-img. Bootstrap's figure component is a
                simple semantic wrapper that provides consistent spacing between the image and
                any caption below it. The Specialization parameter can add Bootstrap image
                utilities such as img-fluid or rounded.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="figure-image-daisyui">DaisyUI Figure &amp; Image</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Figure &amp; Image</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the Figure component is used inside Card components as the card's
                image area. The figure element receives no additional DaisyUI-specific class
                beyond the default figure semantic element, while the Img inside it can receive
                Tailwind responsive utilities. When used inside a Card, the figure sits above
                the CardBody and DaisyUI styles the image-to-body transition automatically.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="figure-image-basecoat">Basecoat Figure &amp; Image</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Figure &amp; Image</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the Figure and Img components are styled with Tailwind utility
                classes. The Img component can receive responsive width and height utilities
                through the Class or Specialization parameters. Basecoat does not apply
                opinionated default styling to figure elements, giving you full control over
                the image presentation through Tailwind utilities.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("figure-image", "Figure & Image"),
    new TocItem("img", "Img", 2),
    new TocItem("figure", "Figure", 2),
    new TocItem("parameters", "Parameters", 2),
    new TocItem("figure-image-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5", 2),
    new TocItem("figure-image-daisyui", "DaisyUI", 2),
    new TocItem("figure-image-basecoat", "Basecoat", 2)
])" />

</div>
